197
00:21:58,791 --> 00:22:02,192
We're often asked to fit our work around crazy production schedules.

198
00:22:02,252 --> 00:22:06,654
But I think as writers, we sometimes have to advocate for that importance of that time and just

199
00:22:07,114 --> 00:22:11,995
uninterrupted time, because I really do believe the most important work happens in your subconscious.

200
00:22:12,536 --> 00:22:18,457
And if you don't have that time to think and to gestate, and you're always on that next deadline, you're not going to access the deep work.

201
00:22:19,798 --> 00:22:21,398
And that's what those four months gave me.

202
00:22:21,618 --> 00:22:28,380
